title: The Nits - Urk
description:
The Nits - Urk / 29 Songs Recorded Live In Amsterdam, Utrecht & Moscow In The Winter Of 1988-1989 (2CD) Release 16-10-1989.

tracklist

The train / Adieu sweet Bahnhof / J.O.S. Days / Sketches of Spain / In the Dutch mountains / The dream / The swimmer / The house / Two skaters / Cabins / Pelican & Penquin / Telephone song / Dapperstreet / Port of Amsterdam / Bike in head / Mountain Jan / Walter & Connie / A touch of Henry Moore / The bauhaus chair / Under a canoe / Shadow of a doubt / Mask / Home before dark / The panorama man / Slip of the tongue / An eating house / Red tape / Tons of ink.


a little info:

Formed in 1974 in Amsterdam, by four art students, the Nits were originally very influenced by sixties British pop as well as bands like XTC, Talking Heads or Kraftwerk. Twenty-five years and nineteen albums on, they are still going strong, although the only original member remaining is singer Henk Hofstede. Their career is paved with little treasures, like 1987 In The Dutch Mountains, their magnificent live album, Urk, released a year later, or thecrystal sciseled beauty Ting in 1992.

Wool is their latest album.

enjoy!
